'''Daniel Solomon "Davey" Crockett''' ([[October 3]], [[1875]] - [[February 23]], [[1961]]) was a [[Major League Baseball]] player for the [[Detroit Tigers]] in 1901 -- the Tigers' first season as a major league team. Born in [[Roanoke, Virginia]], Crockett played in 28 games (27 as a [[first baseman]]) for the Tigers. He hit .284 with a .336 on base percentage and had 29 hits, 14 [[RBI]]s, 10 runs scored, 2 doubles and 2 triples. Crockett died in 1961 at age 85 in [[Charlottesville, Virginia]]. Crockett's name is carved in a stone outside [[Comerica Park]] in Detroit.

